title: NYC GOP councilwoman arrested for bringing gun to pro-Palestinian rally
description: Inna Vernikov’s arrest comes as the week-long war between Israel and Hamas ignites passions across the United States.

title: Politicians called them ‘traitors.’ Now they’re manning Israel’s home front.
description: A group of Israeli veterans opposed to the far-right government are putting politics aside to assist in the war effort.

title: Israel vows ‘complete victory’ over Hamas as Gaza crisis deepens
description: Israel’s national security chief suggested a ground offensive was a certainty, saying Israel could not accept Hamas as a “sovereign entity in the Gaza Strip.”

title: Hundreds of thousands flee south in Gaza after Israel orders evacuation
description: Hundreds of thousands flee south in Gaza even as others refuse to obey an Israeli evacuation order.

title: Palestinian Americans in Washington on edge watching Gaza news
description: For many Palestinians and Palestinian Americans, the days following the horrific assault by Hamas militants on Israel last weekend have been filled with worry.

title: New Zealand votes for change as center-right parties set to form coalition
description: The center-right National Party and the libertarian ACT Party, which have both promised to cut spending and taxes, appear able to form a government.

title: What to know about Poland’s election, Europe’s most-watched vote of 2023
description: Poland’s parliamentary election on Sunday has potential ramifications for Europe, the war in Ukraine and democracy itself.

title: Australian vote to give Indigenous peoples a voice to parliament fails
description: The failure of the “Voice to Parliament” referendum was widely expected but nevertheless comes as a blow to Aboriginal Australians, who have been marginalized since colonization.

title: After facing death, injured Ukrainian soldiers relearn intimacy
description: New guidebooks help wounded soldiers reestablish their sex lives after life-altering wounds including lost limbs.

title: Israel-Gaza war live updates: Israel prepares for ground assault as deadline looms for Gaza
description: The deadline approached for Israel’s order for Gazans to leave the northern part of the enclave. The Red Cross called for a halt to the fighting.

title: Reuters journalist killed in southern Lebanon by Israeli strike, colleagues say
description: Issam Abdalla, 37, a Beirut-based video journalist, had covered conflicts in Syria and Ukraine and was remembered by as a “kind and heartwarming” person.
